/Helvetica-Bold 15 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 693 Tm
(18. Questions Evaluators May Ask) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica-Bold 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 656 Tm
(Q1. Which model did you train?) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 624 Tm
(Logistic Regression inside a Pipeline with StandardScaler. I also used SMOTE and balanced) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 610 Tm
(class weighting to handle class imbalance.) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica-Bold 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 587 Tm
(Q2. Why did you choose Logistic Regression?) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 555 Tm
(It is fast, lightweight, interpretable, and deploys easily in a serverless environment. It) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 541 Tm
(is a strong baseline for binary classification.) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica-Bold 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 518 Tm
(Q3. What is the threshold and why is it 0.35?) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 486 Tm
(The model outputs probabilities. I tuned the decision threshold over several values and) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 472 Tm
(selected 0.35 because it gave the best F1 score on the held-out test set of the synthetic) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 458 Tm
(dataset.) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica-Bold 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 435 Tm
(Q4. Why are the metrics perfect?) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 403 Tm
(Because the training and test data are synthetic and deliberately structured. That proves) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 389 Tm
(the pipeline works, but it is not the same as claiming real-world production accuracy.) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica-Bold 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 366 Tm
(Q5. How do you explain a detection?) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 334 Tm
(The backend adds reasons such as repeated failed logins, suspicious service ports, abnormal) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 320 Tm
(byte ratio, unusual flags, and high packet rate. It also labels the threat category and) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 306 Tm
(recommended disposition.) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica-Bold 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 283 Tm
(Q6. What happens if the model file is missing on Vercel?) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 251 Tm
(The backend enters heuristic fallback mode so the app still scores traffic and remains) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 237 Tm
(demo-ready.) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica-Bold 12 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 214 Tm
(Q7. Where are alerts stored?) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 182 Tm
(Alerts are stored in SQLite locally. On Vercel, the database file is placed in /tmp, so it) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 48 168 Tm
(is temporary.) Tj
ET
BT
/Helvetica-Bold 12 Tf
